body:
I have a RTL design with inputs signals larger than 32 bits.  I read in [[1]](https://www.veripool.org/boards/2/topics/2166-Verilator-How-to-set-an-input-127-0-value-from-C-) that the signals more than 32 bits must be assigned like nibbles of 32 bits (array in cpp).
My systemverilog module (top) has a input signal with 70 bits width and then in my sim_main.cpp I assigned in while loop as:
```
...
 Vtop* top = new Vtop
...
while (!Verilated::gotFinish()) {
...
    for (ii == 0; ii<3; ii++)
	top->i_data[ii] = (int32_t)main_time;

   std::cerr << "i_data (LSB):\t" << top->i_data[0] << "\n";
...
top->eval();
}
..-
```
I tried to print the signal value and I got the same value all time (run clock) but I didn't this problem with other inputs signals (less than 32 bits width).

How I must be assign value to input signals with more than 32 bits width?
